{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17622738","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17622738"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:05:09+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:05:09+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16821"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16821","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16821"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9512"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114431"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9512","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9512"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16821"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96432"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"7166"},{"type":"tags","id":"7180"},{"type":"tags","id":"8509"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22472"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22477"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114431","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114431"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe recurrent meningeal nerve (sinuvertebral nerve) provides important sensory innervation to structures within the vertebral canal.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the recurrent meningeal nerve?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Present at vertebral levels C1-T12 only","Present at vertebral levels T12-S1 only","Branches from the dorsal ramus","Innervates the anterior dura mater and posterior longitudinal ligament","Innervates the posterior aspect of the dura mater"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe recurrent meningeal nerve (sinuvertebral nerve) \u003Cstrong\u003Einnervates the anterior dura mater and posterior longitudinal ligament\u003C/strong\u003E. It provides sensory innervation to the anterior dura mater, posterior longitudinal ligament, periosteum, and intervertebral discs. The nerve branches from the ventral ramus of the spinal nerve, often receiving contributions from the sympathetic nervous system, and is present at all vertebral levels (C1 to S1). It specifically innervates the anterior dura mater, unlike other nerves involved in innervating the posterior dura.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe nerve is not limited to specific segments like C1-T12 or T12-S1 as it is present at all vertebral levels. It branches from the ventral ramus rather than the dorsal ramus, and it innervates the anterior rather than posterior aspect of the dura mater. The recurrent meningeal nerve is clinically important as it carries nociceptive signals from the anterior vertebral canal structures, making it relevant in conditions like disc herniation and spinal stenosis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The recurrent meningeal nerve (sinuvertebral nerve) is present at all vertebral levels and innervates structures within the vertebral canal.","The recurrent meningeal nerve is a branch of the ventral ramus and gray ramus communicans at each spinal level.","The recurrent meningeal nerve provides sensory innervation to the anterior dura mater, posterior longitudinal ligament, and intervertebral discs."],"references":["Shayota B, Wong TL, Fru D, David G, Iwanaga J, Loukas M, Tubbs RS. A comprehensive review of the sinuvertebral nerve with clinical applications. Anat Cell Biol. 2019 Jun;52(2):128-133. doi: 10.5115/acb.2019.52.2.128. Epub 2019 Jun 30. PMID: 31338228; PMCID: PMC6624329.","Lee SH, Shin KJ, Koh KS, Song WC. Visualization of the tentorial innervation of human dura mater. J Anat. 2017 Nov;231(5):683-689. doi: 10.1111/joa.12659. Epub 2017 Jul 10. PMID: 28695607; PMCID: PMC5643920.","Howard, R., Kullmann, D., Werring, D., \u0026 Zandi, M. (Eds.). (2024). Neurology: a queen square textbook. John Wiley \u0026 Sons.","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96432"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16821"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96432","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/96432"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-16T17:05:43+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-16T17:05:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9512"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114431"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relati